File: Professor Malegapuru William Makgoba, a leading scientist and academic, joined the Eskom board as a non-executive director in 2018 and is the lead independent director. JOHANNESBURG - Professor Malegapuru William Makgoba has been appointed interim chairperson of Eskom. Makgoba replaces Jabu Mabuza who resigned last week. Mabuza cited Eskom's inability to meet power demand for his resignation. READ: Cosatu says Eskom board must face consequences Makgoba, a leading scientist and academic, joined the Eskom board as a non-executive director in 2018 and is the lead independent director. In a statement, government said it was "going through the process of putting in place a reconfigured board".